<h2>AMERICAS RevOps takeaways</h2>
<div class="cohort-block">
<p style="margin: 0 0 8px;"><strong>1. AMERICAS is 13pts behind EMEA despite higher invite reach.</strong> 84% invited vs 80% in EMEA, but only 32% attended vs EMEA's 45%. Marketing is reaching doctors — sellers aren't converting registrations to attendance.</p>
<p style="margin: 0 0 8px;"><strong>2. Mort (15%) and Blazewicz (15%) — direct coaching opportunity.</strong> 80%+ invite rate but &lt;15% attendance. Their doctors are getting invited but not showing up. Specific Sales Excellence action.</p>
<p style="margin: 0 0 8px;"><strong>3. Tenure doesn't explain low attendance.</strong> Bridgman (58 months, 31%), Kaliciak (51 months, 31%), Vacchiano (47 months, 30%) — all veterans with weak attendance. This is a skills gap, not a ramp issue.</p>
<p style="margin: 0;"><strong>4. West is the weakest sales area (29% attended, 79% invite reach).</strong> Lowest invite rate AND lowest attendance in AMERICAS. Compounding problem — marketing AND seller motion both need attention.</p>
